WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:02.741
PREVIOUSLY
ON "THE MENTALIST"...

00:02.785 --> 00:03.873
HELLO.
HI.

00:03.916 --> 00:04.700
YOU WERE WATCHING ME.
YES.

00:04.743 --> 00:06.484
WHY?
IT'S MY JOB.

00:06.528 --> 00:08.225
THAT WAS ERICA FLYNN.
SHE WANTS TO HELP OUT
WITH THE INVESTIGATION.

00:08.269 --> 00:11.837
GREAT. WE SHOULD FAX OVER
THE CASE FILE AND GET HER A GUN.

00:11.881 --> 00:13.143
Patrick: YOU'RE SKILLED
AT GETTING PEOPLE

00:13.187 --> 00:14.753
TO OPEN UP TO YOU,
TO TRUST YOU,

00:14.797 --> 00:16.059
AND THERE'S A QUESTION
WHETHER YOU USE THAT SKILL

00:16.103 --> 00:19.019
TO HELP PEOPLE
OR TO MANIPULATE THEM.

00:19.062 --> 00:21.630
Erica: YOU CAN'T FIND HAPPINESS
AGAIN, EVEN TRUE LOVE.

00:21.673 --> 00:23.023
YOU HAVE TO BE WILLING
TO LET ME HELP YOU.

00:23.066 --> 00:24.807
DID YOU KNOW ERICA
WAS GONNA DO THIS?

00:24.850 --> 00:26.113
TRY TO ESCAPE?
OF COURSE.

00:26.156 --> 00:27.897
I KNOW
YOU HAVE FEELINGS FOR ME.

00:33.076 --> 00:34.599
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

00:34.643 --> 00:36.819
THIS WAS A CAR BOMBING
IN PAKISTAN 14 MONTHS AGO.

00:36.862 --> 00:39.561
7 PEOPLE DIED,
30 INJURED.

00:39.604 --> 00:40.953
[ BEEP ]

00:40.997 --> 00:43.043
EGYPT, EIGHT MONTHS AGO.
14 PEOPLE KILLED.

00:43.086 --> 00:44.653
[ BEEP ]

00:44.696 --> 00:46.089
[ GUNFIRE]

00:46.133 --> 00:48.352
THIS WAS AN ATTACK ON A HOTEL
IN INDONESIA.

00:48.396 --> 00:53.705
ALL OF THESE ARE MADE POSSIBLE
BY THIS MAN -- JAN NEMEC.

00:53.749 --> 00:55.185
SLOVAKIAN.

00:55.229 --> 00:57.666
HE WAS TRAINED BY
THE RUSSIAN MOB AS A TEENAGER.

00:57.709 --> 00:59.015
HE'S BASED IN BEIRUT NOW.

00:59.059 --> 01:00.495
SO, HE'S PART
OF A TERRORIST GROUP?

01:00.538 --> 01:02.062
NOT WITH A FACE
LIKE THAT.

01:02.105 --> 01:04.064
HE'S OBVIOUSLY IN IT
FOR THE MONEY.
CORRECT.

01:04.107 --> 01:06.718
THIS IS DANITRA CASS.
SHE'S C.I.A.

01:06.762 --> 01:09.199
THEY'RE HERE TO ASK FOR
YOUR HELP WITH THE NEMEC CASE.

01:09.243 --> 01:12.550
NEMEC'S A SUPPLIER.
HE SELLS WEAPONS, EXPLOSIVES.

01:12.594 --> 01:14.204
WE'VE BEEN STRUGGLING

01:14.248 --> 01:16.250
TO GET SOLID INTELLIGENCE ON HIM
FOR YEARS, BUT HE'S CAREFUL.

01:16.293 --> 01:18.730
WON'T USE COMPUTERS,
DOESN'T LEAVE A DATA TRAIL.

01:18.774 --> 01:20.558
WELL, YOU MUST HAVE SOMETHING
OR YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE.

01:20.602 --> 01:22.734
A SOURCE IN BEIRUT
CLAIMS THAT NEMEC

01:22.778 --> 01:25.781
JUST SENT A SHIPMENT
OF PASSPORT CHIPS TO THE U.S.

01:25.824 --> 01:27.783
YOU USE THESE CHIPS
TO FORGE PASSPORTS

01:27.826 --> 01:30.133
TO GET PEOPLE IN AND OUT
OF THE COUNTRY UNDETECTED.

01:30.177 --> 01:33.963
OUR INFORMANT SAYS THAT
HE WAS PAID 1.5 MILLION EUROS

01:34.006 --> 01:35.878
BY A JIHADIST GROUP
IN THE PHILIPPINES.

01:35.921 --> 01:37.314
WE THINK
IT'S THE FIRST STEP

01:37.358 --> 01:39.099
TOWARDS AN ATTACK
ON AMERICAN SOIL.

01:39.142 --> 01:42.754
WE NEED TO FIND THESE
PASSPORT CHIPS AND ARREST NEMEC,

01:42.798 --> 01:44.930
AND THAT IS WHY
WE'RE ASKING FOR YOUR HELP.

01:44.974 --> 01:47.107
ACTUALLY,
IT'S BECAUSE OF THIS WOMAN.

01:47.150 --> 01:48.151
[ BEEP ]

01:49.500 --> 01:50.632
ERICA FLYNN?

01:50.675 --> 01:52.416
I UNDERSTAND
YOU'VE DEALT WITH HER.

01:52.460 --> 01:54.201
SHE RAN A DATING SERVICE
IN CALIFORNIA.

01:54.244 --> 01:56.072
WE ARRESTED HER
FOR KILLING HER HUSBAND.

01:56.116 --> 01:58.205
SHE ESCAPED FROM PRISON
ABOUT A YEAR AGO.

01:58.248 --> 01:59.641
SHE'S BEEN ON THE RUN
EVER SINCE.

01:59.684 --> 02:02.774
WELL, SHE RAN INTO NEMEC.
SHE'S HIS GIRLFRIEND.

02:02.818 --> 02:06.082
WHAT EXACTLY WAS YOUR
RELATIONSHIP WITH HER, MR. JANE?

02:06.126 --> 02:07.170
ME? WHY?

02:07.214 --> 02:09.216
BECAUSE WE CONTACTED
MS. FLYNN,

02:09.259 --> 02:12.741
AND SHE'S AGREED TO HELP US
FIND THE CHIPS, ARREST NEMEC

02:12.784 --> 02:15.570
IN EXCHANGE FOR A REDUCED
SENTENCE OF HER MURDER CHARGE.

02:15.613 --> 02:18.094
BUT SHE INSISTS
ON WORKING WITH YOU.

02:18.138 --> 02:19.965
SAYS NO OTHER PERSON
WILL DO.

02:20.009 --> 02:21.184
HMM.

02:21.228 --> 02:23.621
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]EXCUSE ME.

02:23.665 --> 02:25.449
NO OTHER PERSON
WILL DO.

02:25.493 --> 02:26.929
DON'T ASK ME.

02:26.972 --> 02:28.496
ABBOTT, WE GOT THE LINK SET UP
IN YOUR OFFICE.

02:28.539 --> 02:29.497
OKAY, LET'S GO.

02:29.540 --> 02:31.194
JOIN US, PLEASE.

02:31.238 --> 02:33.414
E-ERICA FLYNN'S NOT ASKING
TO WORK WITH ME.

02:33.457 --> 02:34.632
WHY AM I A PART OF THIS?

02:34.676 --> 02:36.156
WELL,
IF JANE GOES TO BEIRUT,

02:36.199 --> 02:37.853
HE'S GONNA NEED A PARTNER
TO GO UNDERCOVER WITH HIM.

02:37.896 --> 02:40.029
YOU'VE DONE IT BEFORE.
SEEMED LIKE A LOGICAL CHOICE.

02:40.072 --> 02:41.683
IS THERE A PROBLEM?I ARRESTED HER.

02:41.726 --> 02:44.164
I DON'T KNOW HOW I FEEL
ABOUT HELPING HER AVOID PRISON.

02:44.207 --> 02:46.470
YEAH, IT'S A --
A TRADEOFF. I KNOW,

02:46.514 --> 02:49.995
BUT IT'S WORTH IT, I THINK,
WITH THE ISSUES AT HAND.

02:50.039 --> 02:50.996
JANE?

02:51.040 --> 02:52.041
ME? NO.
NO PROBLEM.

02:52.084 --> 02:53.477
GOOD.

02:53.521 --> 02:55.958
WELL, LISBON,
IF YOU STILL HAVE CONCERNS,

02:56.001 --> 02:58.569
WE CAN DISCUSS IT
AFTER THE MEETING, OKAY?

03:00.745 --> 03:03.226
HMM.

03:07.535 --> 03:10.407
HERE WE GO.

03:12.931 --> 03:15.891
MS. FLYNN,
EVERYONE'S HERE.

03:15.934 --> 03:18.241
PATRICK.
IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.

03:18.285 --> 03:19.503
AND AGENT LISBON.

03:19.547 --> 03:21.853
HELLO.

03:21.897 --> 03:23.507
UH, WHAT IS THIS ABOUT,
ERICA?

03:23.551 --> 03:25.205
ISN'T IT OBVIOUS?

03:25.248 --> 03:27.685
I NEED YOU.REALLY?

03:27.729 --> 03:29.861
JAN USES A COURIER
TO SEND MESSAGES,

03:29.905 --> 03:31.733
BUT THEY'RE CODED.

03:31.776 --> 03:33.648
THE COURIER HAS TO MEMORIZE
A LONG STRING OF NUMBERS.

03:33.691 --> 03:36.085
I CAN'T THINK OF ANYONE WITH
A BETTER MEMORY THAN YOURS.

03:36.128 --> 03:38.218
NEMEC'S COURIER WAS KILLED
IN AN ACCIDENT.

03:38.261 --> 03:39.915
HE'S LOOKING
FOR A NEW ONE.

03:39.958 --> 03:42.483
HE HAS TO LET THE PEOPLE
THAT BOUGHT THE PASSPORT CHIPS

03:42.526 --> 03:44.049
KNOW WHERE
TO PICK THEM UP.

03:44.093 --> 03:46.356
WE'D LIKE YOU TO GO TO BEIRUT
AND BE THE COURIER.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.402
HE'LL GIVE YOU THE CODE,
WE'LL CRACK IT,

03:48.445 --> 03:49.577
GET THE CHIPS, AND HIM.

03:49.620 --> 03:52.928
WELL,
I GUESS I COULD DO THAT.

03:52.971 --> 03:55.583
WONDERFUL.

03:55.626 --> 03:57.585
SEE YOU WHEN YOU GET HERE.

03:57.628 --> 04:00.892
I LOOK FORWARD TO WORKING
WITH YOU AGAIN, PATRICK.

04:00.936 --> 04:02.894
INTERESTING WOMAN.

04:02.938 --> 04:04.679
SIR?
HMM?

04:04.722 --> 04:06.681
THERE'S NO NEED TO MEET.
IT'S AN IMPORTANT MISSION.

04:06.724 --> 04:08.509
I'M HAPPY TO BE A PART OF IT.
IT'S NO PROBLEM.

04:08.552 --> 04:10.380
NO?NONE AT ALL.

04:10.424 --> 04:13.470
SO, WE'RE ALL GOOD, THEN?YEAH, WE'RE GOOD.

04:19.607 --> 04:24.960
♪♪♪

04:24.960 --> 04:29.617
♪♪♪

05:06.001 --> 05:09.134
THANK YOU.

05:09.178 --> 05:10.440
YOU KNOW
WHAT THEY HAVE HERE?

05:10.484 --> 05:11.963
GREAT ORANGE BLOSSOM
ICE CREAM.

05:12.007 --> 05:13.400
OH, THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

05:13.443 --> 05:15.315
YEAH, WE'LL GET SOME.

05:27.892 --> 05:29.503
HERE WE ARE.
HERE WE GO.

05:29.546 --> 05:31.200
[ BEEPING ]

05:31.243 --> 05:33.507
WOW.

05:34.812 --> 05:36.466
PATRICK. WELCOME.[ DOOR CLOSES ]

05:36.510 --> 05:38.338
TERESA,
IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.

05:38.381 --> 05:39.817
HI.
ERICA.

05:39.861 --> 05:41.297
I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU'D BE HERE.

05:41.341 --> 05:43.081
I THOUGHT WE SHOULD TALK
AS SOON AS YOU GOT IN.

05:43.125 --> 05:44.082
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

05:44.126 --> 05:45.388
NOT AT ALL.

05:45.432 --> 05:47.608
I HAD THEM PREPARE TEA.

05:47.651 --> 05:48.870
SO THOUGHTFUL.

05:51.002 --> 05:52.613
TERESA, MAY I?

05:52.656 --> 05:54.310
NO, THANKS.

05:54.354 --> 05:56.138
SO, THE FBI.

05:56.181 --> 05:57.792
THAT'S QUITE
AN ACCOMPLISHMENT.

05:57.835 --> 05:59.228
MS. FLYNN,
IF YOU DON'T MIND,

05:59.271 --> 06:00.925
I'D LIKE TO ASK YOU
A COUPLE QUESTIONS.

06:00.969 --> 06:03.406
OF COURSE.
ERICA, PLEASE.

06:03.450 --> 06:05.800
HOW DID YOU GET INVOLVED
WITH JAN NEMEC?

06:05.843 --> 06:08.324
IT'S KIND OF EMBARRASSING,
ACTUALLY.

06:08.368 --> 06:10.979
I RAN INTO SOME TROUBLE
IN SAO PAULO --

06:11.022 --> 06:12.154
MONEY TROUBLE.

06:12.197 --> 06:13.416
YOU'RE IN
A FOREIGN COUNTRY,

06:13.460 --> 06:14.896
CUT OFF FROM EVERYTHING
YOU KNOW.

06:14.939 --> 06:16.593
YOU KNOW HOW DIFFICULT IT IS
TO LIVE LIKE THAT.

06:16.637 --> 06:18.595
WELL, I THINK YOU WERE BORN
TO LIVE LIKE THAT.

06:18.639 --> 06:20.336
YOU FLATTER ME.

06:20.380 --> 06:22.947
JAN WAS VERY CHARMING,
AND HE WANTED TO HELP.

06:22.991 --> 06:27.299
WE STARTED SEEING EACH OTHER,
FELL INTO TRAVELING TOGETHER.

06:27.343 --> 06:30.128
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT HE DOES FOR A LIVING.

06:30.172 --> 06:31.826
HE TOLD ME
HE WAS A BUSINESSMAN.

06:31.869 --> 06:33.610
AND YOU BELIEVED HIM?

06:33.654 --> 06:36.178
HE'S VERY SECRETIVE
ABOUT HIS WORK.

06:36.221 --> 06:39.834
I SUSPECTED IT WAS UNSAVORY,
MAYBE ILLEGAL,

06:39.877 --> 06:41.662
BUT NOT WHAT
IT ACTUALLY INVOLVES.

06:41.705 --> 06:43.838
WHEN THE C.I.A. TOLD ME,
I WAS HORRIFIED.

06:43.881 --> 06:45.666
AND THAT'S WHY
YOU'RE TURNING HIM IN --

06:45.709 --> 06:47.711
BECAUSE
HE HORRIFIES YOU?

06:47.755 --> 06:52.716
NO. MAINLY BECAUSE
I WANT TO GO BACK HOME.

06:52.760 --> 06:54.762
I MISS IT
MORE THAN I THOUGHT I WOULD.

06:54.805 --> 06:55.850
YOU'RE HOMESICK.

06:55.893 --> 06:57.460
IS THAT SO STRANGE?

06:57.504 --> 06:59.027
WHEN YOU WERE AWAY, WEREN'T
THERE THINGS THAT YOU MISSED

06:59.070 --> 07:02.030
THAT YOU WOULD HAVE GIVEN
ANYTHING TO GET BACK?

07:02.073 --> 07:04.336
YEAH. THERE --
THERE WERE.

07:05.729 --> 07:09.254
I CAN SEE YOU DON'T
BELIEVE ME, TERESA.

07:09.298 --> 07:10.604
I JUST HOPE
THAT IN TIME,

07:10.647 --> 07:12.519
YOU'LL SEE THAT
I'M TELLING THE TRUTH.

07:13.476 --> 07:15.478
WE SHOULD GO SEE JAN.
HE'S EXPECTING YOU.

07:15.522 --> 07:17.915
OKAY.
PATRICK HAS TO
GO ALONE.

07:17.959 --> 07:20.570
HE'S VERY SUSPICIOUS. HE DOESN'T
EVEN KNOW YOU'RE HERE.

07:20.614 --> 07:22.877
I DON'T THINK
I LIKE THIS.

07:22.920 --> 07:24.531
DON'T WORRY.
IT'LL -- IT'LL BE FINE.

07:24.574 --> 07:26.228
LEAD THE WAY.

07:26.271 --> 07:27.795
EXCUSE ME.

07:30.972 --> 07:34.758
SO, YOU AND LISBON ARE TOGETHER,
AS IN A COUPLE?

07:34.802 --> 07:36.934
I CAN TELL BY THE WAY
SHE LOOKS AT YOU

07:36.978 --> 07:40.590
THAT YOU HAVE MORE THAN
A PROFESSIONAL RELATIONSHIP.

07:40.634 --> 07:43.593
THAT IS, IN FACT,
CORRECT, YES.

07:43.637 --> 07:45.290
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU,
PATRICK.

07:45.334 --> 07:46.770
THANK YOU.FOR BOTH OF YOU.

07:46.814 --> 07:49.294
BUT ESPECIALLY FOR YOU.

07:49.338 --> 07:51.296
I KNOW HOW MUCH
YOU WANTED LOVE IN YOUR LIFE.

07:51.340 --> 07:53.951
I'M VERY HAPPY
YOU FOUND IT.

07:53.995 --> 07:55.605
WHAT IS THIS REALLY ABOUT,
ERICA?

07:55.649 --> 07:57.128
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

07:57.172 --> 07:59.130
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

07:59.174 --> 08:01.481
I TOLD YOU.
I WANT TO GO HOME.

08:01.524 --> 08:04.614
YES, BUT THERE'S
SOMETHING ELSE.

08:04.658 --> 08:05.789
YOU'RE WRONG.

08:05.833 --> 08:07.399
BUT THANK YOU
FOR SUSPECTING ME.

08:07.443 --> 08:10.968
[ CHUCKLES ]MAKES ME FEEL
VERY INTERESTING.

08:11.012 --> 08:13.275
THESE MEN WILL TAKE YOU
TO JAN.

08:13.318 --> 08:15.582
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

08:15.625 --> 08:17.279
YES.COME.

08:19.673 --> 08:22.980
GUESS I'LL SEE YOU
A LITTLE LATER.

08:23.024 --> 08:24.504
GOOD LUCK, PATRICK.

08:48.310 --> 08:51.095
[ SHOUTS IN RUSSIAN ][ HORNS HONKING ]

08:52.662 --> 08:54.490
[ HORN BLARES ][ TIRES SCREECH ]

