10:00.904 --> 10:02.732
HI. I'M HERE TO SEE
JAN NEMEC.

10:02.776 --> 10:05.213
[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

10:05.256 --> 10:06.823
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

10:11.959 --> 10:13.438
UH, WHERE ARE WE GOING?

10:13.482 --> 10:16.398
I-I DON'T NEED TO
GO TO THE BATHROOM.

10:16.441 --> 10:18.618
OKAY.

10:20.620 --> 10:23.057
WHAT -- WHAT IS THIS?

10:23.100 --> 10:26.408
WHAT IS -- WHAT IS THIS,
UH, ALL ABOUT HERE?

10:26.451 --> 10:28.715
UH, LISTEN GUYS, IF YOU WERE
PLANNING ON SCARING ME,

10:28.758 --> 10:30.455
THEN MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.
I AM -- I'M SCARED.

10:30.499 --> 10:32.762
AM I -- AM I GONNA GET TO SEE
MR. NEMEC?

10:32.806 --> 10:34.459
LISTEN.I'M LISTENING.

10:34.503 --> 10:38.725
LISTEN. HELICOPTER.
ELECTRIC RANGE. NEWFOUNDLAND.

10:38.768 --> 10:41.553
ALBINO. RETROVIRUS.
WHEELBARROW.

10:41.597 --> 10:42.990
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

10:48.648 --> 10:50.171
OKAY, WHAT -- WHAT --

10:50.214 --> 10:54.697
BATTERY. TRACTOR. FOX.
HYPOTENUSE. SLENDER. ELM.

10:54.741 --> 10:56.612
AAH!

10:56.656 --> 10:59.615
[ GURGLING ]

11:00.660 --> 11:04.098
STOP!
STOP, PLEASE. STOP.

11:04.141 --> 11:08.015
STONE. HARMONY.
LINT. BANANA. LADDER.

11:08.668 --> 11:12.019
[ GRUNTS ]

11:22.203 --> 11:26.120
[ GASPING ]

11:26.163 --> 11:29.297
OKAY. OKAY.[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

11:31.386 --> 11:35.607
[ PANTING ]

11:39.524 --> 11:42.484
[ GROANS ]

11:42.527 --> 11:44.486
PATRICK JANE, RIGHT?

11:44.529 --> 11:47.315
JAN.

11:47.358 --> 11:49.665
JAN NEMEC.

11:49.709 --> 11:52.537
SORRY. THAT WAS PRETTY NASTY,
I KNOW.

11:52.581 --> 11:56.541
STILL, I NEED YOU TO REPEAT
THE WORDS HE JUST SAID TO YOU

11:56.585 --> 11:57.804
IN ORDER.

11:57.847 --> 12:00.154
A TOWEL.

12:00.197 --> 12:02.330
YEAH, SURE.
FIRST THE WORDS.

12:02.373 --> 12:03.810
I WANT A TOWEL.

12:05.725 --> 12:09.119
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

12:11.252 --> 12:14.385
THANK YOU.

12:14.429 --> 12:18.738
HELICOPTER. ELECTRIC RANGE.
NEWFOUNDLAND.

12:18.781 --> 12:22.829
ALBINO. RETROVIRUS.
WHEELBARROW. BATTERY.

12:22.872 --> 12:26.006
TRACTOR.
FOX. HYPOTENUSE.

12:26.049 --> 12:29.183
SLENDER. ELM. STONE.

12:29.226 --> 12:33.840
HARMONY. LINT.
BANANA.

12:33.883 --> 12:35.189
LADDER.

12:35.232 --> 12:37.191
ERICA SAID YOUR MEMORY WAS GOOD.
SHE'S RIGHT.

12:37.234 --> 12:38.366
JUST A TRICK.

12:38.409 --> 12:39.846
NO, I TESTED OTHERS.

12:39.889 --> 12:41.761
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
GETTING EVERYTHING CORRECT.

12:41.804 --> 12:44.024
I DIDN'T SAY
IT WAS AN EASY TRICK.

12:44.067 --> 12:46.548
LIKE I SAID,
UH, I'M SORRY.

12:46.591 --> 12:49.029
PLEASE.

12:49.072 --> 12:51.727
LET'S HAVE SOMETHING
TO DRINK.

12:51.771 --> 12:53.511
I'D RATHER TALK
ABOUT THE JOB.

12:53.555 --> 12:56.993
NAH. YOU DON'T
WANT TO HAVE A DRINK?

12:57.037 --> 12:59.953
WHAT KIND OF A MAN ARE YOU,
JANE?

13:01.737 --> 13:04.696
OKAY. THE JOB.

13:04.740 --> 13:07.525
I NEED YOU TO CARRY
A MESSAGE UP HERE.

13:07.569 --> 13:09.179
[ SNIFFS ]

13:09.223 --> 13:10.354
WHAT KIND OF MESSAGE?

13:10.398 --> 13:12.182
81 UNRELATED NUMBERS.

13:12.226 --> 13:14.750
YOU'LL HAVE TO MEMORIZE THEM.
THEY CANNOT BE WRITTEN DOWN.

13:14.794 --> 13:16.404
WHEN YOU GET
TO THE OTHER END,

13:16.447 --> 13:17.709
YOU'LL HAVE TO REPEAT THEM
IN PRECISE ORDER.

13:17.753 --> 13:18.972
OTHERWISE, IT'S USELESS.

13:19.015 --> 13:20.800
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?
WHAT'S IT ABOUT?

13:20.843 --> 13:23.106
OH, THAT'S EXACTLY
THE POINT.

13:23.150 --> 13:24.368
YOU DON'T KNOW.

13:24.412 --> 13:26.893
WHAT ARE YOU PAYING?

13:26.936 --> 13:28.590
10,000 EUROS.

13:28.633 --> 13:30.418
IF IT WORKS OUT,
THERE'S GONNA BE MORE.

13:30.461 --> 13:32.246
15,000.
10,000.

13:32.289 --> 13:34.204
20,000,
JUST FOR GETTING ME WET.

13:34.248 --> 13:37.468
[ CHUCKLES ]
10,000.

13:37.512 --> 13:40.558
GET SOMEONE ELSE.
I'M NOT INTERESTED.

13:46.651 --> 13:50.090
ERICA SAID
YOU WERE AN ACTOR.

13:52.527 --> 13:54.659
SORT OF.
AND A POLICEMAN?

13:54.703 --> 13:56.879
YEAH,
I WORKED WITHTHE POLICE.

13:56.923 --> 13:58.925
THERE WAS SOMETHING
I WANTED.

13:58.968 --> 14:00.622
AND WHEN I GOT IT,
I LEFT.

14:00.665 --> 14:02.798
BECAUSE YOU KILLED SOMEONE,
SHE SAID.

14:02.842 --> 14:05.279
MORE THAN ONE...
ACTUALLY.

14:05.322 --> 14:06.802
BUT WHO'S COUNTING?

14:06.846 --> 14:08.804
YOU KNOW, IF YOU WANT TO
CHECK ME OR LOOK ME UP,

14:08.848 --> 14:10.850
IT'S ON THE INTERNET.

14:10.893 --> 14:14.114
OH, WE HAVE...PATRICK.

14:14.157 --> 14:16.159
WE HAVE.

14:16.203 --> 14:18.683
RELAX.

14:18.727 --> 14:20.816
EVERYTHING LOOKS OKAY.

14:20.860 --> 14:22.644
ERICA SAYS
YOU'RE A GOOD GUY.

14:22.687 --> 14:24.689
MM.
IT'S ALL GOOD.

14:24.733 --> 14:28.302
UH, I HAVE
ONLY ONE QUESTION, THOUGH.

14:28.345 --> 14:31.218
WHO'S THIS?

14:33.002 --> 14:35.657
AND, UH,
WHY IS SHE WITH YOU?

14:37.137 --> 14:38.921
HI.

14:51.586 --> 14:55.372
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

14:55.416 --> 14:56.721
WHY ARE YOU WET?

14:56.765 --> 15:01.204
THAT'S A LITTLE...
GAG OF JAN'S HERE.

15:01.248 --> 15:04.207
JAN NEMEC, THIS IS
MY GIRLFRIEND, TERESA LISBON.

15:04.251 --> 15:05.948
WE TRAVELED TOGETHER.

15:05.992 --> 15:09.604
SO, UH...WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN BEIRUT?

15:09.647 --> 15:11.911
PATRICK THOUGHT IT WOULD BE
A GOOD IDEA.

15:11.954 --> 15:13.216
SHE HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH THIS.

15:13.260 --> 15:14.914
COULD SHE JUST GO BACK
TO THE HOTEL, PLEASE?

15:14.957 --> 15:16.480
YOU CAN
ASK ME ANYTHING.

15:16.524 --> 15:20.920
WELL, MAYBE YOU CAN TELL ME
IF YOU'RE WITH THE FBI.

15:20.963 --> 15:22.573
NO. WHY?
WHAT?

15:22.617 --> 15:25.228
WELL, IT SAYS HERE,
FBI WEBSITE,

15:25.272 --> 15:28.449
THERE'S A SPECIAL AGENT
TERESA LISBON.

15:28.492 --> 15:30.277
IT'S A MISTAKE.
THAT'S CRAZY.

15:30.320 --> 15:31.408
CHECK AGAIN.

15:31.452 --> 15:32.932
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

15:32.975 --> 15:34.455
WHAT'S THAT?

15:34.498 --> 15:36.587
SOMEONE'S SEARCHING FOR LISBON
IN AN FBI DATABASE.

15:36.631 --> 15:37.762
IS THAT A PROBLEM.

15:37.806 --> 15:39.764
NO,
WE'RE SET UP FOR IT.

15:39.808 --> 15:41.766
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

15:48.817 --> 15:50.819
HMM.

15:50.862 --> 15:51.994
DIFFERENT WOMAN.

15:52.038 --> 15:53.039
TOLD YOU.

15:53.082 --> 15:56.564
YEAH.
SORRY. MISTAKE.

15:56.607 --> 15:58.087
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
NO HARM DONE.

15:58.131 --> 15:59.828
YEAH, WELL,
WE'RE GOING BACK TO THE HOTEL.

15:59.871 --> 16:02.004
IF YOU NEED TO TALK TO ME,
YOU KNOW WHERE TO FIND ME.

16:06.139 --> 16:08.358
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

16:12.493 --> 16:14.277
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

16:14.321 --> 16:15.757
METROPOLE HOTEL.

16:15.800 --> 16:18.325
[ SIGHS ]

16:26.463 --> 16:29.684
WYLIE SUGGESTED BUILDING
THE FAKE PROFILE.

16:29.727 --> 16:34.515
So, now when they see any other
mention of Teresa Lisbon,

16:34.558 --> 16:36.517
They'll assume
it's that woman.

16:36.560 --> 16:38.693
TELL WYLIE
I OWE HIM ONE.

16:38.736 --> 16:41.478
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK?
IS NEMEC ON THE HOOK?

16:41.522 --> 16:42.697
IT'S HARD TO TELL.

16:42.740 --> 16:45.961
JANE MADE AN IMPRESSION.
THAT WE KNOW.

16:46.005 --> 16:47.267
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

16:48.355 --> 16:50.531
WE'LL GET BACK TO YOU.

16:56.841 --> 16:59.192
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

16:59.235 --> 17:02.108
FINE.YOU HAVE A LOT OF NERVE
SHOWING UP HERE.

17:02.151 --> 17:04.458
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?YOU TOLD NEMEC ABOUT ME.

17:04.501 --> 17:06.503
IT WAS YOU. YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO KNOWS I'M HERE.

17:06.547 --> 17:07.983
OF COURSE I DID.

17:08.027 --> 17:10.681
WHY?SHE'S TRYING
TO GAIN NEMEC'S TRUST.

17:10.725 --> 17:12.509
YES.

17:12.553 --> 17:15.164
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO CONVINCE JAN
TO HIRE PATRICK.

17:15.208 --> 17:17.166
HE WAS SUSPICIOUS,
SO TELLING HIM ABOUT YOU

17:17.210 --> 17:19.212
ONLY HELPED PROVE
THAT I'M TRUSTWORTHY.

17:19.255 --> 17:20.517
YOU SHOULD HAVE TOLD US.

17:20.561 --> 17:22.476
I'M SORRY.
I WAS WORKING FAST.

17:22.519 --> 17:24.086
I ASSUMED
YOU WOULD BE PREPARED

17:24.130 --> 17:25.696
FOR THE POSSIBILITY THAT
HE WOULD FIND OUT ABOUT YOU.

17:25.740 --> 17:27.046
WE ARE.

17:27.089 --> 17:29.874
GOOD. BECAUSE IT WORKED.
HE'S DOWNSTAIRS.

17:29.918 --> 17:31.398
HE'S READY
TO MAKE THE DEAL.

17:31.441 --> 17:33.182
DO YOU MIND
IF I STAY UP HERE?

17:33.226 --> 17:34.879
HE DOESN'T
WANT ME DOWN THERE.

17:36.403 --> 17:38.709
OKAY.

17:40.233 --> 17:41.538
I'LL BE GOING.

17:41.582 --> 17:44.367
BYE, Y'ALL.

17:44.411 --> 17:47.544
GET A LITTLE ROOM SERVICE.

17:47.588 --> 17:49.024
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

17:49.981 --> 17:52.027
[ SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE ]

18:00.905 --> 18:03.299
NO, PATRICK.

18:12.439 --> 18:14.658
[ SIGHING ]

18:18.619 --> 18:21.578
OKAY.

18:21.622 --> 18:22.797
20,000.

18:22.840 --> 18:25.321
BUT I NEED YOU TO GO
RIGHT AWAY.

18:25.365 --> 18:28.281
5,000 NOW.
15,000 WHEN YOU COME BACK.

18:30.413 --> 18:32.372
WHERE AM I GOING?
THE U.S.

18:32.415 --> 18:34.417
ATLANTA, GEORGIA.

18:34.461 --> 18:37.116
YOU NEED TO GO TONIGHT,
TOMORROW AT THE LATEST.

18:37.159 --> 18:38.682
WHEN YOU GET THERE,
CALL THIS NUMBER.

18:38.726 --> 18:41.424
GUY WHO ANSWERS
WILL SAY HIS NAME IS JOHN PAUL.

18:41.468 --> 18:45.559
WHEN HE GIVES YOU THAT NAME,
YOU SAY "DAD SENDS HIS LOVE."

18:45.602 --> 18:47.169
HE'LL SAY
"I MISS HIM."

18:47.213 --> 18:49.084
THAT MEANS EVERYTHING IS FINE
AND YOU CAN MEET.

18:49.128 --> 18:50.607
HE'LL TELL YOU
AN ADDRESS.

18:50.651 --> 18:52.435
YOU GO THERE,
GIVE HIM A MESSAGE.

18:52.479 --> 18:54.916
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]
JOB DONE.

18:54.959 --> 18:57.223
WHAT'S THE MESSAGE?

19:00.835 --> 19:03.272
LEFT TO RIGHT, TOP TO BOTTOM,
IN ORDER.

19:03.316 --> 19:05.448
CAN I HAVE A FEW MINUTES?

19:05.492 --> 19:06.667
YEAH, SURE.

19:14.327 --> 19:15.545
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:18.896 --> 19:21.508
ERICA SAYS YOU'RE THE SMARTEST
MAN SHE EVER MET.

19:21.551 --> 19:22.509
HMM.

19:22.552 --> 19:24.511
YEAH.

19:24.554 --> 19:27.427
NEVER HEARD HER SAY THAT
ABOUT ANYONE ELSE.

19:30.647 --> 19:32.780
[ SIGHS ]

19:32.823 --> 19:35.957
YOU HAD HER, RIGHT?

19:37.828 --> 19:40.135
I'M WORKING.

19:40.179 --> 19:41.876
OF COURSE.

19:49.144 --> 19:51.842
[ SPEAKS LEBANESE ]

19:54.062 --> 19:56.195
YOU SPEAK LEBANESE?

19:56.238 --> 19:58.675
JUST ENOUGH TO SAY
"PLEASE" AND "THANK YOU."

19:58.719 --> 19:59.850
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME?

19:59.894 --> 20:01.417
I'M GOOD.

20:03.550 --> 20:06.857
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND ME
SAYING SO, BUT I'M VERY HAPPY

20:06.901 --> 20:08.990
THAT YOU AND PATRICK
HAVE FOUND EACH OTHER.

20:09.033 --> 20:13.168
PATRICK LIKES TO PRETEND
THAT HE'S THIS LONE WOLF.

20:13.212 --> 20:16.171
HE'S NEEDED SOMEONE IN HIS LIFE
EVER SINCE HIS WIFE DIED.

20:16.215 --> 20:17.520
I'M VERY GLAD IT'S YOU.

20:17.564 --> 20:19.087
DID HE SAY SOMETHING
TO YOU?

20:19.130 --> 20:22.264
I USED TO BE
A MATCHMAKER.

20:22.308 --> 20:24.571
I CAN TELL WHEN SOMEONE
IS STARTING A NEW RELATIONSHIP.

20:24.614 --> 20:26.225
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL THING
TO SEE.

20:26.268 --> 20:31.317
WELL...THANKS.

20:31.360 --> 20:35.364
I ALSO SENSE SOME TENSION
BETWEEN YOU AND I.

20:35.408 --> 20:36.887
AND I REALLY
DON'T WANT THAT.

20:36.931 --> 20:40.064
YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.

20:40.108 --> 20:43.067
WHY WOULD I WORRY?
WHAT?

20:43.111 --> 20:44.895
DID PATRICK NOT SAY
ANYTHING?

20:44.939 --> 20:47.246
ABOUT WHAT?

20:47.289 --> 20:51.554
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN.
SO TYPICAL.

20:51.598 --> 20:54.209
MEN LIKE TO PRETEND
LIKE THE PAST NEVER HAPPENED.

20:54.253 --> 20:56.559
WE'RE THE ONES
WHO REMEMBER.

20:58.474 --> 21:00.607
I SHOULDN'T
HAVE SAID ANYTHING.

21:00.650 --> 21:03.262
PLEASE FORGIVE ME.

21:07.831 --> 21:08.963
Patrick: 54.

21:09.006 --> 21:10.965
[ WATER RUNNING ]

21:11.008 --> 21:13.228
10.

21:13.272 --> 21:16.057
300.[ WATER STOPS ]

21:16.100 --> 21:19.365
28.

21:19.408 --> 21:21.236
6.

21:21.280 --> 21:22.977
THAT'S 81 NUMBERS.

21:23.020 --> 21:24.935
MR. JANE,
ARE YOU SURE ABOUT THESE?

21:24.979 --> 21:26.633
THERE'S A LOT HANGING
ON THIS.

21:26.676 --> 21:28.025
YES, I'M SURE.

21:28.069 --> 21:29.418
ALL RIGHT.
WE GOT IT FROM HERE, BUDDY.

21:29.462 --> 21:32.160
YOU GOT A PLANE TO CATCH
TOMORROW. LAY LOW, OKAY?

21:32.203 --> 21:33.814
WILL DO.

21:33.857 --> 21:35.206
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

21:35.250 --> 21:36.599
WHEW!

21:36.643 --> 21:38.340
YOU KNOW, I'M NOT THAT TIRED.
HOW ABOUT YOU?

21:38.384 --> 21:40.081
NO.
WANT TO GO
GET SOMETHING TO EAT?

21:40.124 --> 21:42.388
BELLBOY WAS TELLING ME
ABOUT THIS RESTAURANT

21:42.431 --> 21:43.780
THAT DOES A GREAT MANAKISH.

21:43.824 --> 21:46.261
YEAH, SURE.

21:48.263 --> 21:51.353
EVERYTHING OKAY?
FINE.

21:51.397 --> 21:52.963
OKAY.

21:53.007 --> 21:55.139
YOUR LIAISON --
GIVE HIM THE NUMBERS

21:55.183 --> 21:57.620
AND ANY OTHER SUPPORT
THAT THEY ASK FOR.

21:57.664 --> 21:59.796
TELL VEGA TO STAY CLOSE
AND GIVE YOU THE HELP YOU NEED.

21:59.840 --> 22:01.624
GOT IT.

22:01.668 --> 22:04.148
AND WHAT IF
THEY CAN'T CRACK IT?

22:04.192 --> 22:05.324
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

22:05.367 --> 22:08.152
THIS GUY, JOHN PAUL,

22:08.196 --> 22:10.154
DOES HE HAVE ANY IDEA
WHEN JANE'S SUPPOSED TO ARRIVE

22:10.198 --> 22:11.808
IN THE U.S.?
NO.

22:11.852 --> 22:13.984
AND NEMEC WON'T RISK
GETTING IN TOUCH WITH HIM.

22:14.028 --> 22:15.812
JANE SAID HE WAS ONLY GIVEN
A WINDOW OF ARRIVAL,

22:15.856 --> 22:17.466
NOT A SPECIFIC DATE.

22:17.510 --> 22:19.338
SO, AS FAR AS HE KNOWS,
JANE'S ALREADY HERE.

22:19.381 --> 22:20.643
DOES HE KNOW
WHAT JANE LOOKS LIKE?

22:20.687 --> 22:22.819
NO. HE DOESN'T.

22:22.863 --> 22:23.994
SO, LET'S SET UP
THE MEET.

22:24.038 --> 22:25.692
WE GET THE MESSAGE
TO JOHN PAUL,

22:25.735 --> 22:27.346
WE FOLLOW HIM
TO THE LOCATION,

22:27.389 --> 22:29.652
WE GRAB HIM
AND THE PASSPORT CHIPS,

22:29.696 --> 22:31.654
EVEN IF
HE CAN'T CRACK THE CODE.

22:31.698 --> 22:33.526
IS THAT OKAY
WITH THE C.I.A.?

22:33.569 --> 22:35.832
AS LONG AS
WE'RE IN ON IT.

22:35.876 --> 22:37.704
OUR PLEASURE.

22:41.403 --> 22:43.013
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

22:43.057 --> 22:44.058
THIS IS JOHN PAUL.

22:44.101 --> 22:45.146
DAD SENDS HIS LOVE.

22:45.189 --> 22:46.408
I MISS HIM.

22:46.452 --> 22:47.975
WHERE SHOULD I GO?YOU'RE IN ATLANTA?

22:48.018 --> 22:48.976
YES.

22:49.019 --> 22:51.979
How soon can you meet?

22:52.022 --> 22:53.154
FIVE HOURS.

22:55.939 --> 22:59.900
THERE'S A ROADHOUSE
IN BROOKHAVEN.

22:59.943 --> 23:02.424
LITTLE ED'S ON WALTHROP.

23:02.468 --> 23:04.034
TURN YOUR COFFEE CUP
UPSIDE DOWN.

23:04.078 --> 23:05.949
OKAY.

23:10.519 --> 23:13.348
FIRE UP THE JET.

23:13.392 --> 23:15.394
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

23:17.047 --> 23:19.006
SO, ANYWAY,
THE ANALYSTS ARE TRYING

23:19.049 --> 23:21.008
SOMETHING CALLED
MODULO-2 ARITHMETIC,

23:21.051 --> 23:22.531
WHICH SOUNDS VERY COOL.

23:22.575 --> 23:24.533
I JUST WISH
I KNEW WHAT IT MEANT.

23:27.449 --> 23:29.233
HELLO?
HMM?

23:29.277 --> 23:31.235
SORRY, UH,
WHAT WERE YOU SAYING?

23:31.279 --> 23:32.367
NOTHING.

23:33.934 --> 23:35.544
LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE
GETTING READY FOR THE MEET.

23:35.588 --> 23:37.764
YEP.

23:37.807 --> 23:39.374
PRETTY EXCITING,
I GUESS.

23:39.418 --> 23:42.029
YEAH.

23:42.072 --> 23:45.424
ANYWAY, UM,
HOW CAN I HELP YOU HERE?

23:45.467 --> 23:47.469
YOU SHOULD GO WITH CHO.
I DON'T NEED YOUR HELP.

23:47.513 --> 23:48.688
NO.NO, DON'T WORRY.

23:48.731 --> 23:49.906
IT'S FINE.
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

23:49.950 --> 23:51.604
YOU MEAN IT?
YEAH. SURE.

23:51.647 --> 23:53.606
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE THE BEST.

23:53.649 --> 23:54.998
OF COURSE.

23:55.042 --> 23:58.088
SIR. AGENT WYLIE
DOESN'T NEED MY HELP.

23:58.132 --> 23:59.568
OKAY IF I COME ALONG
WITH YOU?

23:59.612 --> 24:01.091
YOU RUN IT BY ABBOTT?
DID HE OKAY IT?

24:01.135 --> 24:03.093
YES, SIR, HE DID.

24:03.137 --> 24:04.268
SUIT UP.
WE LEAVE RIGHT AWAY.

24:19.196 --> 24:21.155
ONLY TWO MINUTES
PAST THE TARGET HOUR.

24:21.198 --> 24:23.070
Everybody stay loose.

24:30.033 --> 24:31.731
MALE, 30s, FROM THE NORTH.

24:31.774 --> 24:33.559
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:33.602 --> 24:35.778
THERE SHE IS.HEY!

24:35.822 --> 24:36.910
FALSE ALARM.

24:50.967 --> 24:53.492
ANOTHER MALE.

24:53.535 --> 24:55.145
LATE 20s,
POSSIBLY FILIPINO.

25:02.501 --> 25:03.937
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

25:03.980 --> 25:05.199
[ BELL JINGLES ]

25:19.518 --> 25:23.391
HEY. HEY,
EVERYBODY STAY CALM.

25:43.106 --> 25:44.238
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

25:46.370 --> 25:47.502
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

25:47.546 --> 25:49.156
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

25:51.419 --> 25:54.248
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

25:55.249 --> 25:56.685
YOU BITCH![ GUN COCKS ]

25:57.730 --> 26:00.994
VEGA!

26:01.864 --> 26:03.910
YOU OKAY?

26:03.953 --> 26:05.912
YEAH.

26:23.364 --> 26:26.062
OH, THANK YOU.

26:29.239 --> 26:31.546
WHAT?

26:31.590 --> 26:32.852
WHAT WAS THAT THING
YOU SAID WAS GOOD?

26:32.895 --> 26:34.854
IT WAS MANA SOMETHING?MANAKISH.

26:34.897 --> 26:37.378
OH.
YEAH,
IT'S LIKE A LITTLE PIZZA.

26:37.421 --> 26:40.381
OH.

26:40.424 --> 26:41.687
WHAT'S UP?

26:41.730 --> 26:44.385
NOTHING.

26:44.428 --> 26:46.822
NOTHING.

26:51.871 --> 26:54.656
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN
BETWEEN YOU AND ERICA FLYNN?

26:54.700 --> 26:56.484
WHY?

26:56.527 --> 27:01.402
SHE MADE A POINT OF LETTING ME
KNOW THAT IT DID, SO DID IT?

27:01.445 --> 27:04.405
UH...

27:04.448 --> 27:07.582
WELL, UM...

27:07.626 --> 27:10.063
ACTUALLY, YES.
SOMETHING DID.

27:10.106 --> 27:12.065
OH.

27:12.108 --> 27:14.676
WHEN WE WERE WORKING TOGETHER,
WE -- WE KISSED.

27:14.720 --> 27:16.678
YOU KISSED?
JUST ONCE
IN HER HOTEL ROOM.

27:16.722 --> 27:19.420
THIS STORY JUST KEEPS ON
GETTING BETTER.

27:19.463 --> 27:20.551
IT WAS NOTHING.

27:20.595 --> 27:21.857
DON'T SAY THAT, OKAY?

27:21.901 --> 27:23.032
OKAY, WELL,
YOU'RE RIGHT.

27:23.076 --> 27:26.209
IT -- IT WASN'T NOTHING
AT THE TIME.

27:26.253 --> 27:30.039
BUT IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO,
AND, UM...

27:30.083 --> 27:31.693
IT WAS NEVER GONNA AMOUNT
TO ANYTHING.

27:31.737 --> 27:33.216
IT JUST --
IT -- IT COULDN'T.

27:33.260 --> 27:36.393
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?I DIDN'T THINK ABOUT IT.

27:36.437 --> 27:38.265
WELL, WHEN YOU FOUND OUT
WE WERE COMING HERE,

27:38.308 --> 27:39.266
YOU COULD HAVE TOLD ME.

27:39.309 --> 27:40.659
YES,
I THOUGHT ABOUT IT THEN,

27:40.702 --> 27:43.444
BUT I-I MADE A DECISION...
NOT TO TELL YOU

27:43.487 --> 27:49.755
BECAUSE I WAS WORRIED THAT,
UM...

27:49.798 --> 27:51.844
THAT IT WOULD
COME BETWEEN US.

27:51.887 --> 27:54.716
I JUST WISH I'D HEARD IT
FROM YOU FIRST.

27:54.760 --> 27:56.413
THAT'S ALL.

27:56.457 --> 27:59.155
I UNDERSTAND.

28:00.635 --> 28:05.596
YEAH, UH...
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU.

28:05.640 --> 28:06.728
I'M SORRY.

28:06.772 --> 28:08.599
IT'S OKAY.

28:08.643 --> 28:11.690
REALLY. IT'S OKAY.

28:14.649 --> 28:17.260
ARE THERE ANY OTHERS
THAT I SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?

28:17.304 --> 28:18.958
LIKE,
PEOPLE WE'VE WORKED WITH?

28:19.001 --> 28:21.047
IT WOULD -- IT WOULD HELP ME
IF I -- IF I KNEW.NO.

28:21.090 --> 28:22.744
LORELEI?

28:22.788 --> 28:25.747
I ALWAYS THOUGHT THAT MAYBE
SOMETHING HAPPENED WITH YOU TWO.

28:25.791 --> 28:26.922
LORELEI?

28:26.966 --> 28:29.229
UH-HUH.

28:32.188 --> 28:34.495
OKAY, HOW ABOUT THIS?

28:34.538 --> 28:36.976
I'LL TELL YOU
ABOUT LORELEI

28:37.019 --> 28:39.326
IF YOU WOULD TELL ME
ABOUT ONE WALTER MASHBURN.

28:43.025 --> 28:45.332
Y-YOU SAID THAT MANAKISH
IS LIKE A LITTLE PIZZA?

28:45.375 --> 28:46.812
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.
YUM.

28:46.855 --> 28:48.161
LET'S GET SOME.
YEAH.

28:48.204 --> 28:50.511
TEA?

28:50.554 --> 28:51.817
PLEASE.

28:51.860 --> 28:52.992
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

28:53.035 --> 28:54.907
IS THAT YOUR PHONE?

28:59.955 --> 29:01.783
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]WHAT'S UP, BOSS?

29:01.827 --> 29:03.089
ABBOTT:
We've got a problem.

29:03.132 --> 29:05.308
HIS FULL NAME
IS JOHN PAUL NAVARRO.

29:05.352 --> 29:06.745
LOOKS LIKE HE WAS CONNECTED

29:06.788 --> 29:08.311
TO A JIHADIST GROUP
IN THE PHILIPPINES.

29:08.355 --> 29:10.096
WE'RE STILL
LOOKING INTO THAT.

29:10.139 --> 29:12.098
Well, what about
the blank passport chips?

29:12.141 --> 29:14.448
WELL, LOOKS LIKE
THEY'RE IN THE ATLANTA AREA,

29:14.491 --> 29:15.841
BUT WE JUST DON'T KNOW WHERE.

29:15.884 --> 29:17.930
UH, HOW'S THE C.I.A. DOING
WITH THE CODE?

29:17.973 --> 29:20.497
THEY CAN'T CRACK IT.
THEY THINK IT'S A ONE-TIME PAD.

29:20.541 --> 29:21.672
WHAT'S THAT?

29:21.716 --> 29:23.805
I-It's a-a code made
with a key.

29:23.849 --> 29:25.328
THE PERSON WHO ENCODES
THE MESSAGE HAS THE KEY,

29:25.372 --> 29:28.157
SO DOES THE PERSON
WHO DECODES IT.

29:28.201 --> 29:29.550
WITHOUT IT,
YOU CAN'T MAKE SENSE OF IT.

29:29.593 --> 29:31.204
NEMEC AND JOHN PAUL
MUST HAVE THE KEY.

29:31.247 --> 29:32.858
DID YOU CHECK
JOHN PAUL'S APARTMENT?

29:32.901 --> 29:35.034
YEAH, BUT WE NEED TO KNOW
WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR.

29:35.077 --> 29:37.819
IT COULD BE ANYTHING --
A MAGAZINE, A BOOK.

29:37.863 --> 29:39.168
IT'S A BOOK.

29:39.212 --> 29:40.866
Why?

29:40.909 --> 29:43.956
WELL, NEMEC HAS TWO BOOKSHELVES
FILLED, AND HE'S NOT A READER.

29:43.999 --> 29:45.696
WE STILL NEED TO KNOW
WHICH BOOK IT IS.

29:45.740 --> 29:48.699
SO, IN THE MEANTIME, YOU TWO
NEED TO GET OUT OF THERE.

29:48.743 --> 29:50.701
PRETTY SOON,
NEMEC IS GONNA FIND OUT

29:50.745 --> 29:52.878
THAT JOHN PAUL IS DEAD,
AND WHEN HE DOES,

29:52.921 --> 29:54.401
YOU TWO NEED TO
STAY OUT OF SIGHT.

29:54.444 --> 29:56.707
CHANGE HOTELS,
STAY INDOORS,

29:56.751 --> 29:59.014
and get on that plane
tomorrow.

29:59.058 --> 30:00.668
YEAH, WE'LL DEFINITELY
DO ALL OF THAT,

30:00.711 --> 30:02.583
BUT I THINK WE CAN FIND
THOSE COMPUTER CHIPS.

30:02.626 --> 30:03.714
HOW?

30:03.758 --> 30:05.716
UH, I'LL TELL YOU LATER.
BYE.

30:05.760 --> 30:07.718
[ Click ]WHAT'S YOUR PLAN?

30:07.762 --> 30:09.720
UH, THE KEY IS PROBABLY
IN ONE OF THE BOOKS

30:09.764 --> 30:10.983
IN NEMEC'S APARTMENT.

30:11.026 --> 30:12.549
I JUST NEED TO FIGURE OUT
WHICH ONE.

30:12.593 --> 30:13.855
WELL, HOW ARE WE GONNA
GET INTO THE APARTMENT?

30:13.899 --> 30:15.509
TAXI!

30:15.552 --> 30:17.076
DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE CALLING HER.

30:17.119 --> 30:18.164
I AM.WE DON'T NEED HER HELP.

30:18.207 --> 30:19.600
YES, WE DO.

30:19.643 --> 30:22.429
HEY, ERICA, IT'S PATRICK.
SORRY TO WAKE YOU.

30:22.472 --> 30:25.606
YEP. YEP.

30:34.136 --> 30:37.009
JAN'S GOT A MEETING ACROSS TOWN.
IT SHOULD BE FINE.

30:39.925 --> 30:42.057
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

30:42.101 --> 30:43.537
[ KEYPAD BEEPS ]

30:43.580 --> 30:46.366
[ BEEPING STOPS ]

30:46.409 --> 30:48.281
DO YOU NEED HELP?

30:48.324 --> 30:49.804
UH, YEAH.

30:49.848 --> 30:52.938
N-NO, ACTUALLY. I --
I'M -- I'M FINE, THANK YOU.

30:52.981 --> 30:54.200
[ SIGHS ]

30:54.243 --> 30:55.592
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR?

30:55.636 --> 30:56.942
SORT OF.

30:56.985 --> 30:59.205
I ALWAYS THINK
OF YOU AS HAVING A PLAN

30:59.248 --> 31:00.728
BUT NEVER ADMITTING IT.

31:00.771 --> 31:02.034
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S FUNNY.

31:02.077 --> 31:04.471
THAT'S
HOW I THINK OF YOU.

31:04.514 --> 31:06.821
[ SIGHS ]

31:06.865 --> 31:07.953
HOW MUCH LONGER?

31:07.996 --> 31:10.042
NOT TOO MUCH LONGER.

31:10.085 --> 31:11.565
BE PATIENT.

31:14.133 --> 31:16.439
HE'S HERE. HE'S BACK.

31:16.483 --> 31:20.052
[ GROANS ]

31:20.095 --> 31:21.270
[ KEYPAD BEEPS ]

31:21.314 --> 31:23.359
[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

31:25.622 --> 31:29.061
LIGHT.
LIGHT, LIGHT, LIGHT, LIGHT.

31:32.194 --> 31:35.502
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

31:35.545 --> 31:38.331
[ KEYPAD BEEPS ]

31:38.374 --> 31:40.072
[ BEEPING STOPS ]

31:44.728 --> 31:48.297
[ ZIPPER OPENS ]

31:53.346 --> 31:55.391
[ URINATING ]

31:59.830 --> 32:03.095
[ PANTING ]

32:03.138 --> 32:04.966
I THINK WE'RE FINE.

32:05.010 --> 32:11.103
WHEW!
THAT WAS CLOSE.

32:11.146 --> 32:12.321
[ CHUCKLING ]

32:18.806 --> 32:21.243
I'M SORRY
YOU DIDN'T GET YOUR BOOK.

32:21.287 --> 32:23.942
OH, NO.
I GOT -- I GOT MY BOOK.

32:23.985 --> 32:25.508
RIGHT HERE.

32:26.901 --> 32:29.730
LET'S GO.

32:34.909 --> 32:36.867
EXCUSE ME, SIR?

32:36.911 --> 32:37.999
YEAH,
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

32:38.043 --> 32:39.696
WELL,
THE C.I.A. ANALYSTS THINK

32:39.740 --> 32:42.003
THE CODE TREATS
EACH BOOK PAGE LIKE A GRID,

32:42.047 --> 32:44.005
SO THE FIRST NUMBER
TELLS YOU WHAT PAGE NUMBER,

32:44.049 --> 32:46.007
THE SECOND'S THE NUMBER
OF LETTERS ACROSS THE BOTTOM,

32:46.051 --> 32:47.400
THE THIRD'S THE NUMBER
OF LETTERS UP.

32:47.443 --> 32:49.010
EACH THREE-NUMBER SET
GIVES YOU ONE LETTER.

32:49.054 --> 32:50.316
YEAH,
HOW LONG TO WORK IT OUT?

32:50.359 --> 32:52.144
IF THEY'RE RIGHT,
10 MINUTES.

32:52.187 --> 32:54.059
CALL CHO
AS SOON AS YOU GOT IT.

33:00.239 --> 33:02.981
FBI! OPEN UP!

33:14.079 --> 33:15.863
Man: CLEAR!

33:15.906 --> 33:17.517
CLEAR!

33:17.560 --> 33:19.040
Man #2: CLEAR!

33:19.084 --> 33:22.043
Vega: CLEAR UPSTAIRS!

33:22.087 --> 33:24.045
DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
ANYBODY'S BEEN HERE FOR A WHILE.

33:24.089 --> 33:26.134
YOU SURE YOUR PEOPLE
GOT THE RIGHT ADDRESS?

33:28.136 --> 33:29.790
ANY SIGN
OF THE CHIPS UPSTAIRS?

33:29.833 --> 33:32.097
NO.
BUT THEY'RE LOOKING.

33:32.140 --> 33:34.099
MAYBE WE WANT TO BRING IN
SOME TECHS,

33:34.142 --> 33:35.970
START TEARING UP
THE FLOORBOARDS.

33:36.014 --> 33:37.537
THEY COULD BE ANYWHERE.

33:41.628 --> 33:43.064
ARE THE SHADES DRAWN
UPSTAIRS?

33:43.108 --> 33:44.239
I THINK SO.

33:44.283 --> 33:46.285
THIS ONE ISN'T.

33:59.950 --> 34:01.648
GUESS THIS IS
THE RIGHT ADDRESS.

34:13.138 --> 34:15.270
THAT'S GREAT.

34:15.314 --> 34:16.967
WHAT ABOUT THE GROUP
JOHN PAUL BELONGED TO?

34:17.011 --> 34:18.752
DID WE GET ANYTHING
ON THEM?

34:18.795 --> 34:20.145
FROM WHAT WE CAN TELL,

34:20.188 --> 34:21.450
MOST OF THE MEMBERSHIP'S
IN THE PHILIPPINES.

34:21.494 --> 34:23.539
PRETTY LOW LEVEL,
BARELY ON THE RADAR,

34:23.583 --> 34:25.411
BUT WE HAVE OUR EYES
ON THEM NOW.

34:25.454 --> 34:28.979
TELL ME, HOW DID JANE KNOW
WHICH BOOK IT WAS?

34:29.023 --> 34:31.112
IT HAD TO HAVE BEEN A BOOK
THAT NEMEC HAD READ RECENTLY,

34:31.156 --> 34:33.027
SO HE LOOKED FOR ONE
THAT HAD A CRACKED SPINE,

34:33.071 --> 34:34.507
THAT DIDN'T HAVE
ANY DUST ON IT.

34:34.550 --> 34:37.249
NICE.
NEMEC IN CUSTODY YET?

34:37.292 --> 34:40.817
THE BEIRUT POLICE
ARE ARRESTING HIM NOW.

34:40.861 --> 34:43.820
YOU THINK YOU GET AWAY?!
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

34:43.864 --> 34:46.475
I'LL FIND YOU, ERICA!
I'LL FIND YOU!

34:46.519 --> 34:49.826
I'LL CUT OFF YOUR HEAD
AND I'LL SPIT DOWN YOUR NECK,

34:49.870 --> 34:53.308
YOU LITTLE BITCH!

34:53.352 --> 34:55.919
[ SHOUTING IN RUSSIAN ]

35:05.015 --> 35:06.539
JANE?

35:08.193 --> 35:10.325
I WAS JUST HELPING ERICA
FOR A MOMENT.

35:10.369 --> 35:11.544
HELPING HER?

35:11.587 --> 35:14.373
[ SIGHS ] YES.
JAN WAS FURIOUS.

35:14.416 --> 35:16.505
IT WAS VERY UPSETTING.

35:16.549 --> 35:19.334
OKAY.

35:19.378 --> 35:21.293
A BEIRUT POLICE OFFICER WILL
TAKE YOU INTO PROTECTIVE CUSTODY

35:21.336 --> 35:22.990
UNTIL THE EMBASSY
CAN ARRANGE FOR YOU

35:23.033 --> 35:25.035
TO BE ESCORTED
BACK TO THE U.S.

35:25.079 --> 35:27.168
OKAY. THAT'S FINE.

35:27.212 --> 35:29.475
JANE, CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

35:29.518 --> 35:31.390
SURE.

35:34.219 --> 35:36.525
LOOK, LISBON,
SHE'S JUST VERY UPSET.

35:36.569 --> 35:38.658
WELL, I DON'T WANT TO
TALK ABOUT HER.

35:38.701 --> 35:41.008
THIS IS ABOUT YOU.
YOU LIED ABOUT KISSING HER.

35:41.051 --> 35:42.314
I DIDN'T LIE.

35:42.357 --> 35:43.750
AND YOU INSISTED
ON GETTING HER HELP

35:43.793 --> 35:45.708
EVEN AFTER I SPECIFICALLY
ASKED YOU NOT TO.

35:45.752 --> 35:47.057
I'M WORKING WITH HER.

35:47.101 --> 35:48.668
THAT'S WHAT
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO DO, RIGHT?

35:48.711 --> 35:50.626
EVER SINCE WE GOT HERE,
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT ERICA,

35:50.670 --> 35:52.324
TRYING TO FIND WAYS
TO SPEND TIME WITH HER.

35:52.367 --> 35:54.326
LISBON, THERE'S NO REASON
TO GET EMOTIONAL HERE.

35:54.369 --> 35:55.892
IT'S -- IT'S --
IT'S NOTHING.

35:55.936 --> 35:58.330
WHATEVER HAPPENED
BETWEEN YOU TWO, IT'S NOT OVER.

35:58.373 --> 35:59.505
JUST ADMIT IT.

35:59.548 --> 36:02.072
THAT IS NOT TRUE.
IT'S NOT.

36:02.116 --> 36:04.379
I NEED TO BRING NEMEC IN
WITH THE POLICE.

36:04.423 --> 36:06.816
YOU DO WHAT YOU WANT.
I'M DONE.

36:23.659 --> 36:26.575
UH, I GUESS
THIS IS THE OFFICER

36:26.619 --> 36:30.231
THAT'S SUPPOSED TO TAKE YOU
INTO CUSTODY.

36:30.275 --> 36:32.233
HE'S NOT GOING TO,
IS HE?

36:32.277 --> 36:33.930
NO.

36:33.974 --> 36:35.845
[ SPEAKS LEBANESE ]

36:41.808 --> 36:44.941
YOU ALWAYS HAVE
EVERY ANGLE COVERED.

36:44.985 --> 36:47.944
DON'T YOU?

36:47.988 --> 36:50.556
IT'S HERE, ISN'T IT?
WHAT?

36:50.599 --> 36:51.905
THAT THING
YOU WOULDN'T TELL ME ABOUT --

36:51.948 --> 36:53.602
THE OTHER REASON
YOU DID THIS.

36:53.646 --> 36:55.256
I'M SORRY. I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

36:55.300 --> 36:57.693
THE 1.5 MILLION EURO
NEMEC RECEIVED

36:57.737 --> 36:59.391
FOR THOSE PASSPORT CHIPS.

36:59.434 --> 37:02.959
THE MONEY --
IT'S IN THIS ROOM.

37:03.003 --> 37:04.613
YOU NEEDN'T DENY IT.

37:04.657 --> 37:07.225
YOU'RE THE SMARTEST MAN
I EVER MET.
HMM.

37:14.710 --> 37:16.669
IT'S PRETTY, ISN'T IT?GORGEOUS.

37:16.712 --> 37:18.845
YOU TOOK YOUR CHANCE
WHEN THE C.I.A. CAME TO YOU

37:18.888 --> 37:20.455
ABOUT TURNING NEMEC IN.

37:20.499 --> 37:22.196
THEN YOU HAD
HIS COURIER KILLED

37:22.240 --> 37:23.763
AND YOU MADE IT LOOK LIKE
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

37:23.806 --> 37:25.199
WHY DO YOU ALWAYS THINK
THE WORST OF ME?

37:25.243 --> 37:28.202
AND YOU THOUGHT
THAT YOU COULD USE ME

37:28.246 --> 37:30.900
TO TAKE CARE OF NEMEC
AND TAKE HIS CASH.

37:30.944 --> 37:34.469
AFTER ALL, YOU'D ALREADY GOTTEN
AWAY FROM ME ONCE BEFORE.

37:34.513 --> 37:37.646
YOU NEVER INTENDED
TO GO BACK TO THE U.S.

37:37.690 --> 37:40.301
ALL YOU WANTED
WAS NEMEC'S MONEY AND FREEDOM.

37:40.345 --> 37:41.781
MAYBE YOU'RE NOT AS SMART
AS I THOUGHT.

37:41.824 --> 37:43.086
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

37:43.130 --> 37:44.305
IT WASN'T JUST
ABOUT THE MONEY.

37:44.349 --> 37:45.480
WHAT ELSE?

37:47.047 --> 37:49.267
I MISSED YOU, PATRICK.

37:51.704 --> 37:55.185
I'M A PROFESSIONAL IN THE FIELD
OF ROMANCE AND RELATIONSHIPS.

37:55.229 --> 37:59.320
AND IT PAINS ME TO ADMIT IT,
BUT IN MY PROFESSIONAL OPINION,

37:59.364 --> 38:02.323
YOU AND LISBON WILL NOT LAST
AS A COUPLE.

38:02.367 --> 38:03.846
WHY IS THAT?BECAUSE YOU'RE DRAWN
TO EACH OTHER

38:03.890 --> 38:05.239
FOR THE WRONG REASONS.

38:05.283 --> 38:07.720
YOU'RE ATTRACTED TO HER VIRTUE,
HER HONESTY,

38:07.763 --> 38:10.897
AND HER GOODNESS --
THINGS YOU THINK YOU LACK.

38:10.940 --> 38:13.900
SHE'S INTERESTED IN YOU
FOR YOUR DANGER,

38:13.943 --> 38:18.731
YOUR UNPREDICTABILITY,
YOUR TRANSGRESSIONS.

38:18.774 --> 38:22.343
THESE SUPERFICIAL QUALITIES
ARE ALLURING, EVEN EROTIC,

38:22.387 --> 38:24.345
BUT THEY DON'T MAKE
FOR A LASTING RELATIONSHIP.

38:24.389 --> 38:25.520
AND WHAT DOES?

38:25.564 --> 38:28.871
FINDING YOUR SOUL MATE --

38:28.915 --> 38:32.353
THE PERSON WHO SEES THE WORLD
THE WAY YOU DO,

38:32.397 --> 38:34.529
WHO LAUGHS AT THE THINGS
YOU LAUGH AT,

38:34.573 --> 38:37.837
AND...WANTS THE THINGS
THAT YOU WANT.

38:37.880 --> 38:39.404
AND THAT'S YOU?

38:39.447 --> 38:42.145
HERE I AM.

38:45.148 --> 38:46.759
[ SIGHS ]

38:46.802 --> 38:48.761
I LOVE LISBON.

38:48.804 --> 38:52.286
AND I'M TAKING YOU
TO THE REAL POLICE,

38:52.330 --> 38:54.375
AND THEY'RE GONNA LOCK YOU UP
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

38:54.419 --> 38:57.422
OH, PATRICK.

38:58.640 --> 39:00.381
I TRIED.

39:00.425 --> 39:03.253
[ GRUNTING ]

39:05.908 --> 39:07.432
GOODBYE.

39:13.829 --> 39:15.701
ON YOUR KNEES, ERICA.

39:17.616 --> 39:19.574
DO IT.

39:19.618 --> 39:21.924
[ SIGHS ]

39:25.450 --> 39:26.407
JANE, YOU ALL RIGHT?

39:26.451 --> 39:27.930
[ Straining ] YEAH.

39:27.974 --> 39:29.628
YEP.
I'M OKAY, JUST...

39:29.671 --> 39:30.933
[ GROANS ]

39:33.675 --> 39:35.982
OOH, JUST NEED TO
WALK IT OFF A LITTLE BIT.

39:36.025 --> 39:37.375
[ GROANS ]

39:43.511 --> 39:45.426
Vega:
LISBON SENT THIS?

39:45.470 --> 39:46.732
YEAH.

39:46.775 --> 39:48.124
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
TO HER?

39:48.168 --> 39:49.909
ABBOTT SAYS
THE DEAL'S OFF.

39:49.952 --> 39:50.823
WHEN SHE GETS BACK, SHE'LL SERVE
OUT THE REST OF HER SENTENCE.

39:50.866 --> 39:52.433
VEGA.

39:52.477 --> 39:53.608
COME HERE.

39:53.652 --> 39:54.783
YES, SIR.

39:54.827 --> 39:56.437
SIT DOWN.

40:01.790 --> 40:03.357
YOU DID
GOOD WORK TODAY.

40:03.401 --> 40:05.315
BUT ABBOTT SAYS HE NEVER
APPROVED YOU LEAVING THE OFFICE.

40:05.359 --> 40:07.622
YOU SAID HE DID.

40:07.666 --> 40:08.884
DID YOU LIE TO ME?

40:10.408 --> 40:12.410
SIR, I DI--ANSWER THE QUESTION.

40:13.802 --> 40:16.588
YES.

40:16.631 --> 40:18.111
I'M SORRY.

40:18.154 --> 40:20.853
I KNOW THAT --
I JUST GOT EXCITED, I GUESS,

40:20.896 --> 40:22.376
AND I THOUGHT
THAT I'D BE A LOT MORE --

40:22.420 --> 40:23.769
THAT'S NOT YOUR CALL.

40:23.812 --> 40:26.511
NOW, I CAN'T WORK WITH SOMEONE
I CAN'T TRUST.

40:26.554 --> 40:27.773
YOU CANTRUST ME.

40:27.816 --> 40:29.775
NO, I CAN'T.

40:29.818 --> 40:31.516
YOU'RE NOT GOING OUT
IN THE FIELD WITH ME AGAIN.

40:31.559 --> 40:32.691
FOR HOW LONG?

40:32.734 --> 40:34.693
WE'LL SEE.

40:39.524 --> 40:40.829
HEY.

40:40.873 --> 40:43.441
YOU OKAY?

40:57.542 --> 40:58.847
WHAT ARE WE DOING?

40:58.891 --> 41:00.370
WE NEED TO
GET TO THE AIRPORT.

41:00.414 --> 41:01.763
COME ON. YOU'LL SEE.

41:01.807 --> 41:03.373
IT SAYS WE HAVE TO BE THERE
TWO HOURS EARLY.

41:03.417 --> 41:04.940
OH.

41:09.684 --> 41:12.252
OH, MY GOD. JANE!

41:13.688 --> 41:17.170
IT'S AMAZING.
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:17.213 --> 41:18.650
YOU DID THIS?

41:18.693 --> 41:20.652
OF COURSE.

41:20.695 --> 41:21.653
[ GASPS ]

41:21.696 --> 41:24.525
PLEASE.THANK YOU.

41:24.569 --> 41:27.093
AND...WHAT?

41:31.576 --> 41:35.057
ORANGE BLOSSOM ICE CREAM.
YOU ARE GOOD.

41:35.101 --> 41:36.232
DIG IN.

41:36.276 --> 41:38.626
THANK YOU.

41:41.107 --> 41:43.675
[ EXPLOSIONS ]WHAT'S THAT?

41:43.718 --> 41:44.893
FIREWORKS.

41:44.937 --> 41:47.069
FIREWORKS?

41:47.113 --> 41:48.723
IT'S THE END OF RAMADAN.
THEY'RE CELEBRATING.

41:48.767 --> 41:51.378
FIREWORKS.
BEAUTIFUL.

41:51.421 --> 41:54.555
YEAH.
IT IS BEAUTIFUL.

41:58.341 --> 42:00.605
YOU THOUGHT IT WAS A BOMB,
DIDN'T YOU?

42:00.648 --> 42:01.780
NO, I DIDN'T.

42:01.823 --> 42:04.217
YES, YOU DID.

42:04.260 --> 42:05.392
I DID NOT.

42:05.435 --> 42:06.741
YOU DID.

42:06.785 --> 42:09.048
YOU KNOW, THIS ICE CREAM
IS ONLY JUST OKAY.

42:09.091 --> 42:10.876
DON'T TAKE IT OUT
ON THE ICE CREAM.

42:10.919 --> 42:13.052
I'M JUST SAYING,
IT'S A LONG WAY TO GO

42:13.095 --> 42:15.054
FOR AN OKAY BOWL
OF ICE CREAM.

42:15.097 --> 42:18.405
AS THEY SAY, YOU CAN TAKE
THE GIRL OUT OF CHICAGO,

42:18.448 --> 42:23.062
BUT YOU CAN'T TAKE THE CHICAGO
OUT OF THE GIRL.
